# Home Assistant Configuration Rules

This is a Home Assistant configuration repository. Follow these rules when generating or modifying automations, scripts, and templates.

---

## Modern Automation Syntax (REQUIRED)

Home Assistant has updated its automation syntax. **Always use the modern syntax** described below. The old syntax is deprecated and should not be used.

### Automation Structure

```yaml
automation:
  - id: "unique_automation_id"
    alias: "Descriptive Automation Name"
    description: "Optional detailed description of what this automation does"
    mode: single  # single | restart | queued | parallel
    
    triggers:
      - trigger: <type>
        # trigger configuration
    
    conditions:
      - condition: <type>
        # condition configuration
    
    actions:
      - action: <domain.service>
        # action configuration
```

---

## Triggers

### Modern Syntax (USE THIS)
```yaml
triggers:
  - trigger: state
    entity_id: binary_sensor.motion
    to: "on"
  
  - trigger: time
    at: "07:00:00"
  
  - trigger: time_pattern
    hours: /1
  
  - trigger: event
    event_type: "custom_event"
  
  - trigger: numeric_state
    entity_id: sensor.temperature
    above: 25
  
  - trigger: sun
    event: sunset
    offset: "-00:30:00"
  
  - trigger: template
    value_template: "{{ states('sensor.temp') | float > 30 }}"
  
  - trigger: mqtt
    topic: "home/sensor/temperature"
```

### Old Syntax (DO NOT USE)
```yaml
# ❌ WRONG - Do not use
trigger:
  - platform: state
    entity_id: binary_sensor.motion
    to: "on"
```

### Key Differences
| Old (Deprecated) | Modern (Required) |
|-----------------|-------------------|
| `trigger:` | `triggers:` |
| `platform: state` | `trigger: state` |
| `platform: time` | `trigger: time` |
| `platform: event` | `trigger: event` |

---

## Conditions

### Modern Syntax (USE THIS)
```yaml
conditions:
  - condition: state
    entity_id: input_boolean.enabled
    state: "on"
  
  - condition: numeric_state
    entity_id: sensor.temperature
    below: 30
  
  - condition: time
    after: "06:00:00"
    before: "22:00:00"
    weekday:
      - mon
      - tue
      - wed
      - thu
      - fri
  
  - condition: sun
    after: sunset
    before: sunrise
  
  - condition: template
    value_template: "{{ states('sensor.temp') | float < 25 }}"
  
  - condition: zone
    entity_id: person.john
    zone: zone.home
  
  # Logical conditions
  - condition: and
    conditions:
      - condition: state
        entity_id: light.living_room
        state: "on"
      - condition: numeric_state
        entity_id: sensor.brightness
        below: 50
  
  - condition: or
    conditions:
      - condition: state
        entity_id: input_boolean.guest_mode
        state: "on"
      - condition: state
        entity_id: input_boolean.party_mode
        state: "on"
  
  # Trigger-based condition (for multi-trigger automations)
  - condition: trigger
    id: "morning_trigger"
```

### Old Syntax (DO NOT USE)
```yaml
# ❌ WRONG - Do not use
condition:
  - condition: state
    entity_id: input_boolean.enabled
    state: "on"
```

### Key Differences
| Old (Deprecated) | Modern (Required) |
|-----------------|-------------------|
| `condition:` | `conditions:` |

---

## Actions

### Modern Syntax (USE THIS)
```yaml
actions:
  - action: light.turn_on
    target:
      entity_id: light.living_room
    data:
      brightness: 255
      color_temp: 350
  
  - action: notify.mobile_app
    data:
      title: "Alert"
      message: "Motion detected"
  
  - action: script.my_script
  
  # Variables
  - variables:
      brightness_level: "{{ states('input_number.brightness') | int }}"
  
  # Delays
  - delay:
      seconds: 5
  
  - delay: "00:01:00"
  
  # Wait templates
  - wait_template: "{{ is_state('light.living_room', 'off') }}"
    timeout: "00:05:00"
    continue_on_timeout: true
  
  # Wait for trigger
  - wait_for_trigger:
      - trigger: state
        entity_id: binary_sensor.door
        to: "off"
    timeout: "00:10:00"
  
  # Conditional actions (choose)
  - choose:
      - conditions:
          - condition: state
            entity_id: input_boolean.night_mode
            state: "on"
        sequence:
          - action: light.turn_on
            target:
              entity_id: light.bedroom
            data:
              brightness: 50
    default:
      - action: light.turn_on
        target:
          entity_id: light.bedroom
        data:
          brightness: 255
  
  # If/then/else
  - if:
      - condition: state
        entity_id: sun.sun
        state: "below_horizon"
    then:
      - action: light.turn_on
        target:
          entity_id: light.porch
    else:
      - action: light.turn_off
        target:
          entity_id: light.porch
  
  # Repeat loops
  - repeat:
      count: 5
      sequence:
        - action: light.toggle
          target:
            entity_id: light.alert
        - delay:
            milliseconds: 500
  
  # Stop execution
  - stop: "Condition not met"
    error: false
  
  # Parallel execution
  - parallel:
      - action: light.turn_on
        target:
          entity_id: light.living_room
      - action: media_player.play_media
        target:
          entity_id: media_player.speaker
        data:
          media_content_id: "http://example.com/sound.mp3"
          media_content_type: "music"
```

### Old Syntax (DO NOT USE)
```yaml
# ❌ WRONG - Do not use
action:
  - service: light.turn_on
    entity_id: light.living_room
    data:
      brightness: 255
```

### Key Differences
| Old (Deprecated) | Modern (Required) |
|-----------------|-------------------|
| `action:` | `actions:` |
| `service: light.turn_on` | `action: light.turn_on` |
| `entity_id:` at root level | `target:` with `entity_id:` |

---

## Scripts

Scripts use `sequence:` with the same modern action syntax:

```yaml
script:
  morning_routine:
    alias: "Morning Routine"
    description: "Activates morning settings"
    icon: mdi:weather-sunny
    mode: single
    
    # Optional fields for script parameters
    fields:
      brightness:
        description: "Light brightness level"
        example: 100
        default: 80
        selector:
          number:
            min: 0
            max: 100
    
    sequence:
      - action: light.turn_on
        target:
          entity_id: light.bedroom
        data:
          brightness_pct: "{{ brightness }}"
      
      - action: media_player.volume_set
        target:
          entity_id: media_player.bedroom_speaker
        data:
          volume_level: 0.3
      
      - action: tts.speak
        target:
          entity_id: tts.google_en
        data:
          media_player_entity_id: media_player.bedroom_speaker
          message: "Good morning!"
```

---

## Template Triggers (Trigger-Based Template Sensors)

```yaml
template:
  - trigger:
      - trigger: time_pattern
        hours: /1
    action:
      - action: weather.get_forecasts
        data:
          type: hourly
        target:
          entity_id: weather.home
        response_variable: forecast
    sensor:
      - name: "Hourly Forecast"
        unique_id: hourly_forecast
        state: "{{ now().isoformat() }}"
        attributes:
          forecast: "{{ forecast }}"
```

---

## Trigger IDs

Use trigger IDs to identify which trigger fired in multi-trigger automations:

```yaml
triggers:
  - trigger: state
    entity_id: binary_sensor.front_door
    to: "on"
    id: "front_door"
  
  - trigger: state
    entity_id: binary_sensor.back_door
    to: "on"
    id: "back_door"
  
  - trigger: time
    at: "22:00:00"
    id: "nightly_check"

conditions: []

actions:
  - choose:
      - conditions:
          - condition: trigger
            id: "front_door"
        sequence:
          - action: notify.mobile_app
            data:
              message: "Front door opened"
      
      - conditions:
          - condition: trigger
            id: "back_door"
        sequence:
          - action: notify.mobile_app
            data:
              message: "Back door opened"
      
      - conditions:
          - condition: trigger
            id: "nightly_check"
        sequence:
          - action: script.check_all_doors
```

---

## Target Syntax

Always use `target:` to specify entities, devices, or areas:

```yaml
# ✅ CORRECT - Modern syntax
- action: light.turn_on
  target:
    entity_id: light.living_room
  data:
    brightness: 255

# ✅ CORRECT - Multiple entities
- action: light.turn_off
  target:
    entity_id:
      - light.living_room
      - light.kitchen
      - light.bedroom

# ✅ CORRECT - Target by area
- action: light.turn_on
  target:
    area_id: living_room

# ✅ CORRECT - Target by device
- action: light.turn_on
  target:
    device_id: abc123def456

# ❌ WRONG - Old inline syntax
- action: light.turn_on
  entity_id: light.living_room
  data:
    brightness: 255
```

---

## Complete Example

```yaml
automation:
  - id: "motion_lights"
    alias: "Motion-Activated Lights"
    description: "Turn on lights when motion is detected, with brightness based on time of day"
    mode: restart
    
    triggers:
      - trigger: state
        entity_id: binary_sensor.living_room_motion
        to: "on"
        id: "motion_detected"
      
      - trigger: state
        entity_id: binary_sensor.living_room_motion
        to: "off"
        for:
          minutes: 5
        id: "motion_cleared"
    
    conditions:
      - condition: state
        entity_id: input_boolean.motion_lights_enabled
        state: "on"
    
    actions:
      - choose:
          - conditions:
              - condition: trigger
                id: "motion_detected"
            sequence:
              - if:
                  - condition: sun
                    after: sunset
                    before: sunrise
                then:
                  - action: light.turn_on
                    target:
                      entity_id: light.living_room
                    data:
                      brightness_pct: 30
                      color_temp: 500
                else:
                  - action: light.turn_on
                    target:
                      entity_id: light.living_room
                    data:
                      brightness_pct: 100
                      color_temp: 350
          
          - conditions:
              - condition: trigger
                id: "motion_cleared"
            sequence:
              - action: light.turn_off
                target:
                  entity_id: light.living_room
```

---

## Quick Reference Cheat Sheet

| Component | Old Syntax | Modern Syntax |
|-----------|-----------|---------------|
| Triggers list | `trigger:` | `triggers:` |
| Trigger type | `platform: state` | `trigger: state` |
| Trigger type | `platform: time` | `trigger: time` |
| Trigger type | `platform: event` | `trigger: event` |
| Conditions list | `condition:` | `conditions:` |
| Actions list | `action:` | `actions:` |
| Service call | `service: light.turn_on` | `action: light.turn_on` |
| Entity target | `entity_id: light.x` | `target:` → `entity_id: light.x` |

---

## Common Trigger Types

- `state` - Entity state changes
- `time` - Specific time of day
- `time_pattern` - Recurring time patterns (e.g., every hour)
- `event` - Home Assistant events
- `numeric_state` - Numeric threshold crossings
- `sun` - Sunrise/sunset events
- `template` - Template evaluation changes
- `mqtt` - MQTT messages
- `webhook` - HTTP webhook calls
- `zone` - Zone enter/leave
- `device` - Device-specific triggers
- `calendar` - Calendar events
- `tag` - NFC/QR tag scans
- `sentence` - Voice assistant sentences
- `persistent_notification` - Notification events
- `geolocation` - Geolocation events

---

## Common Condition Types

- `state` - Check entity state
- `numeric_state` - Check numeric value
- `time` - Check time of day
- `sun` - Check sun position
- `zone` - Check if entity in zone
- `template` - Evaluate template
- `trigger` - Check which trigger fired (by ID)
- `and` - All conditions must be true
- `or` - Any condition must be true
- `not` - Negate a condition

